<span id="Usage"></span>
==Utilizzo==

<div class="mw-translate-fuzzy">
#Cliccare su [[Image:FEM_ConstraintTemperature.png|32px]] o scegliere {{KEY|Modello}} → '''Vincoli termici'''  →  {{KEY|[[Image:FEM_ConstraintTemperature.png|32px]] Vincolo temperatura}} dal menu principale.
#Selezionare nella vista 3D  gli oggetti a cui deve essere applicato il vincolo, che possono essere:
## vertici (angoli)
## bordi
## facce
#Inserire una temperatura da applicare agli oggetti.
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
==Properties==
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
* {{PropertyData|Enable Amplitude}} - {{Version|1.1}}: Enables the use of CalculiX's amplitude for the time variation of the temperature boundary condition. At a given time, magnitude of the boundary condition is multiplied by the amplitude value corresponding to that time. Linear interpolation is used between the specified values. Constant values are used outside of the specified range.
* {{PropertyData|Amplitude Values}} - {{Version|1.1}}: Amplitude table in the following format (default - linear increase from 0% at t=0 to 100% at t=1):
</div>

: {{Code|lang=text|code=
time_1, amplitude_value_1
...
}}

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
: Default is linear increase from 0% at t=0 to 100% at t=1:
</div>

: {{Code|lang=text|code=
0, 0
1, 1
}}

